{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":838,"text":"I think the beautiful Malin [Akerman] put it perfectly."},{"time":2812,"text":"Every man deserves the opportunity"},{"time":5152,"text":"to grow a little bit of luxury."}]},{"cues":[{"time":7775,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, and more importantly,"},{"time":9605,"text":"Mo Bros and Mo Sistas — (Laughter) —"},{"time":12458,"text":"for the next 17 minutes, I'm going to share with you"},{"time":14994,"text":"my Movember journey, and how, through that journey,"},{"time":18645,"text":"we've redefined charity, we're redefining the way"},{"time":21816,"text":"prostate cancer researchers are working together"},{"time":24954,"text":"throughout the world, and I hope, through that process,"},{"time":28706,"text":"that I inspire you to create something significant"},{"time":32077,"text":"in your life, something significant that will go on"},{"time":35659,"text":"and make this world a better place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39242,"text":"So the most common question I get asked,"},{"time":42171,"text":"and I'm going to answer it now so I don't have to do it"},{"time":44359,"text":"over drinks tonight, is how did this come about?"},{"time":48832,"text":"How did Movember start?"},{"time":51395,"text":"Well, normally, a charity starts with the cause, and someone"},{"time":54132,"text":"that is directly affected by a cause."},{"time":57194,"text":"They then go on to create an event, and beyond that,"},{"time":60378,"text":"a foundation to support that."},{"time":63548,"text":"Pretty much in every case, that's how a charity starts."},{"time":68251,"text":"Not so with Movember. Movember started in a very"},{"time":71682,"text":"traditional Australian way. It was on a Sunday afternoon."},{"time":75460,"text":"I was with my brother and a mate having a few beers,"},{"time":78048,"text":"and I was watching the world go by,"},{"time":80219,"text":"had a few more beers, and the conversation turned"},{"time":82628,"text":"to '70s fashion — (Laughter) —"},{"time":87000,"text":"and how everything manages to come back into style."},{"time":89908,"text":"And a few more beers, I said, \"There has to be some stuff"},{"time":92204,"text":"that hasn't come back.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":97042,"text":"Then one more beer and it was, whatever happened to the mustache?"},{"time":100564,"text":"Why hasn't that made a comeback? (Laughter)"},{"time":104948,"text":"So then there was a lot more beers, and then the day ended"},{"time":106501,"text":"with a challenge to bring the mustache back. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":111711,"text":"So in Australia, \"mo\" is slang for mustache,"},{"time":114444,"text":"so we renamed the month of November \"Movember\""},{"time":117452,"text":"and created some pretty basic rules, which still stand today."},{"time":120399,"text":"And they are: start the month clean-shaven,"},{"time":123166,"text":"rock a mustache -- not a beard, not a goatee, a mustache --"},{"time":126420,"text":"for the 30 days of November, and then we agreed"},{"time":129195,"text":"that we would come together at the end of the month,"},{"time":131697,"text":"have a mustache-themed party, and award a prize"},{"time":135709,"text":"for the best, and of course, the worst mustache. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":140531,"text":"Now trust me, when you're growing a mustache"},{"time":142005,"text":"back in 2003, and there were 30 of us back then,"},{"time":145210,"text":"and this was before the ironic hipster mustache movement"},{"time":149250,"text":"— (Laughter) —"},{"time":153714,"text":"it created a lot of controversy. (Laughter)"},{"time":158251,"text":"So my boss wouldn't let me go and see clients."},{"time":160546,"text":"My girlfriend at the time, who's no longer my girlfriend — (Laughter) — hated it."},{"time":166882,"text":"Parents would shuffle kids away from us. (Laughter)"},{"time":172542,"text":"But we came together at the end of the month and"},{"time":173989,"text":"we celebrated our journey, and it was a real journey."},{"time":177277,"text":"And we had a lot of fun, and in 2004, I said to the guys,"},{"time":182049,"text":"\"That was so much fun. We need to legitimize this"},{"time":185236,"text":"so we can get away with it year on year.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":190019,"text":"So we started thinking about that, and we were inspired"},{"time":193858,"text":"by the women around us and all they were doing for breast cancer."},{"time":196946,"text":"And we thought, you know what, there's nothing for men's health."},{"time":199407,"text":"Why is that? Why can't we combine growing a mustache"},{"time":203320,"text":"and doing something for men's health?"},{"time":204812,"text":"And I started to research that topic, and discovered"},{"time":207476,"text":"prostate cancer is the male equivalent of breast cancer"},{"time":210390,"text":"in terms of the number of men that die from it and are diagnosed with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213351,"text":"But there was nothing for this cause,"},{"time":215919,"text":"so we married growing a mustache with prostate cancer,"},{"time":220074,"text":"and then we created our tagline, which is,"},{"time":222180,"text":"\"Changing the face of men's health.\""},{"time":224189,"text":"And that eloquently describes the challenge,"},{"time":226928,"text":"changing your appearance for the 30 days,"},{"time":229039,"text":"and also the outcome that we're trying to achieve:"},{"time":230859,"text":"getting men engaged in their health, having them have"},{"time":233495,"text":"a better understanding about the health risks that they face."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237799,"text":"So with that model, I then"},{"time":240479,"text":"cold-called the CEO of the Prostate Cancer Foundation."},{"time":243158,"text":"I said to him, \"I've got the most amazing idea"},{"time":245525,"text":"that's going to transform your organization.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":248719,"text":"And I didn't want to share with him the idea over the phone,"},{"time":251138,"text":"so I convinced him to meet with me for coffee in Melbourne"},{"time":253494,"text":"in 2004."},{"time":255206,"text":"And we sat down, and I shared with him my vision"},{"time":258399,"text":"of getting men growing mustaches across Australia,"},{"time":261119,"text":"raising awareness for this cause,"},{"time":263831,"text":"and funds for his organization. And I needed a partnership"},{"time":266463,"text":"to legitimately do that."},{"time":269040,"text":"And I said, \"We're going to come together at the end,"},{"time":270641,"text":"we're going to have a mustache-themed party, we're going to have DJs,"},{"time":273311,"text":"we're going to celebrate life, and we're going to change the face of men's health.\""},{"time":277114,"text":"And he just looked at me and laughed, and he said,"},{"time":279891,"text":"he said, \"Adam, that's a really novel idea,"},{"time":283526,"text":"but we're an ultraconservative organization."},{"time":286031,"text":"We can't have anything to do with you.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":290847,"text":"So I paid for coffee that day — (Laughter) —"},{"time":295207,"text":"and his parting comment as we shook hands was,"},{"time":298210,"text":"\"Listen, if you happen to raise any money out of this,"},{"time":300873,"text":"we'll gladly take it.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305427,"text":"So my lesson that year was persistence."},{"time":309151,"text":"And we persisted, and we got 450 guys"},{"time":313551,"text":"growing mustaches, and together we raised 54,000 dollars,"},{"time":318719,"text":"and we donated every cent of that to the Prostate Cancer Foundation of Australia,"},{"time":321751,"text":"and that represented at the time the single biggest donation"},{"time":324857,"text":"they'd ever received."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327413,"text":"So from that day forward, my life has become about a mustache."},{"time":332014,"text":"Every day -- this morning, I wake up and go, my life"},{"time":334603,"text":"is about a mustache. (Laughter)"},{"time":338580,"text":"Essentially, I'm a mustache farmer. (Laughter)"},{"time":343563,"text":"And my season is November. (Applause)"},{"time":346828,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":349919,"text":"So in 2005, the campaign got more momentum,"},{"time":353828,"text":"was more successful in Australia and then New Zealand,"},{"time":356269,"text":"and then in 2006 we came to a pivotal point."},{"time":361027,"text":"It was consuming so much of our time after hours"},{"time":364764,"text":"on weekends that we thought, we either need"},{"time":367889,"text":"to close this down or figure a way to fund Movember"},{"time":371203,"text":"so that I could quit my job and go and spend more time"},{"time":374036,"text":"in the organization and take it to the next level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377866,"text":"It's really interesting when you try and figure a way"},{"time":380724,"text":"to fund a fundraising organization"},{"time":382865,"text":"built off growing mustaches. (Laughter)"},{"time":385320,"text":"Let me tell you that there's not too many people interested"},{"time":387691,"text":"in investing in that, not even the Prostate Cancer Foundation,"},{"time":391723,"text":"who we'd raised about 1.2 million dollars for at that stage."},{"time":394988,"text":"So again we persisted, and Foster's Brewing came to the party"},{"time":399123,"text":"and gave us our first ever sponsorship,"},{"time":402263,"text":"and that was enough for me to quit my job, I did consulting on the side."},{"time":406836,"text":"And leading into Movember 2006,"},{"time":411802,"text":"we'd run through all the money from Foster's,"},{"time":414387,"text":"we'd run through all the money I had, and essentially"},{"time":417545,"text":"we had no money left, and we'd convinced all our suppliers --"},{"time":420643,"text":"creative agencies, web development agencies,"},{"time":422836,"text":"hosting companies, whatnot -- to delay their billing until December."},{"time":427289,"text":"So we'd racked up at this stage about 600,000 dollars"},{"time":430319,"text":"worth of debt. So if Movember 2006 didn't happen,"},{"time":434574,"text":"the four founders, well, we would've been broke,"},{"time":437944,"text":"we would've been homeless, sitting on the street"},{"time":439637,"text":"with mustaches. (Laughter)"},{"time":442495,"text":"But we thought, you know what, if that's the worst thing"},{"time":444400,"text":"that happens, so what?"},{"time":446645,"text":"We're going to have a lot of fun doing it, and it taught us"},{"time":448407,"text":"the importance of taking risks and really smart risks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":452905,"text":"Then in early 2007, a really interesting thing happened."},{"time":457168,"text":"We had Mo Bros from Canada, from the U.S.,"},{"time":460887,"text":"and from the U.K. emailing us and calling us and saying,"},{"time":463831,"text":"hey, there's nothing for prostate cancer."},{"time":465815,"text":"Bring this campaign to these countries."},{"time":469317,"text":"So we thought, why not? Let's do it."},{"time":471679,"text":"So I cold-called the CEO of Prostate Cancer Canada,"},{"time":474809,"text":"and I said to him, \"I have this most amazing concept.\""},{"time":478335,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":480103,"text":"\"It's going to transform your organization. I don't want"},{"time":483150,"text":"to tell you about it now, but will you meet with me"},{"time":484614,"text":"if I fly all the way to Toronto?\" So I flew here,"},{"time":488023,"text":"met down on Front Street East, and we sat in the boardroom,"},{"time":491151,"text":"and I said, \"Right, here's my vision of getting men growing mustaches"},{"time":495228,"text":"all across Canada raising awareness and funds for your organization.\""},{"time":499999,"text":"And he looked at me and laughed and said,"},{"time":501240,"text":"\"Adam, sounds like a really novel idea, but we're"},{"time":503598,"text":"an ultraconservative organization.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":506493,"text":"I've heard this before. I know how it goes."},{"time":509500,"text":"But he said, \"We will partner with you,"},{"time":511974,"text":"but we're not going to invest in it. You need to figure"},{"time":515192,"text":"a way to bring this campaign across here and make it work.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":518063,"text":"So what we did was, we took some of the money that"},{"time":519976,"text":"we raised in Australia to bring the campaign across"},{"time":522079,"text":"to this country, the U.S, and the U.K., and we did that"},{"time":524680,"text":"because we knew, if this was successful,"},{"time":527136,"text":"we could raise infinitely more money globally"},{"time":529744,"text":"than we could just in Australia. And that money"},{"time":532279,"text":"fuels research, and that research will get us to a cure."},{"time":535365,"text":"And we're not about finding an Australian cure"},{"time":537119,"text":"or a Canadian cure, we're about finding the cure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541498,"text":"So in 2007, we brought the campaign across here,"},{"time":545806,"text":"and it was, it set the stage for the campaign."},{"time":550351,"text":"It wasn't as successful as we thought it would be."},{"time":552384,"text":"We were sort of very gung ho with our success in Australia"},{"time":555034,"text":"and New Zealand at that stage."},{"time":557855,"text":"So that year really taught us the importance of being patient"},{"time":561359,"text":"and really understanding the local market before you"},{"time":563647,"text":"become so bold as to set lofty targets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567295,"text":"But what I'm really pleased to say is, in 2010,"},{"time":571319,"text":"Movember became a truly global movement."},{"time":573923,"text":"Canada was just pipped to the post in terms of"},{"time":576199,"text":"the number one fundraising campaign in the world."},{"time":578871,"text":"Last year we had 450,000 Mo Bros spread across the world"},{"time":584003,"text":"and together we raised 77 million dollars."},{"time":588055,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":595963,"text":"And that makes Movember now the biggest funder"},{"time":598302,"text":"of prostate cancer research and support programs in the world."},{"time":602545,"text":"And that is an amazing achievement when you think about"},{"time":604894,"text":"us growing mustaches. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":608630,"text":"And for us, we have redefined charity."},{"time":610646,"text":"Our ribbon is a hairy ribbon. (Laughter)"},{"time":616022,"text":"Our ambassadors are the Mo Bros and the Mo Sistas,"},{"time":618379,"text":"and I think that's been fundamental to our success."},{"time":621574,"text":"We hand across our brand and our campaign to those people."},{"time":625678,"text":"We let them embrace it and interpret it in their own way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629622,"text":"So now I live in Los Angeles, because"},{"time":632221,"text":"the Prostate Cancer Foundation of the U.S. is based there,"},{"time":634990,"text":"and I always get asked by the media down there,"},{"time":637518,"text":"because it's so celebrity-driven,"},{"time":640054,"text":"\"Who are your celebrity ambassadors?\""},{"time":642821,"text":"And I say to them, \"Last year we were fortunate enough"},{"time":645622,"text":"to have 450,000 celebrity ambassadors.\""},{"time":649084,"text":"And they go, \"What, what do you mean?\""},{"time":650324,"text":"And it's like, everything single person, every single Mo Bro"},{"time":653286,"text":"and Mo Sista that participates in Movember"},{"time":655877,"text":"is our celebrity ambassador, and that is so, so important"},{"time":659367,"text":"and fundamental to our success."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662286,"text":"Now what I want to share with you is"},{"time":664958,"text":"one of my most touching Movember moments,"},{"time":668958,"text":"and it happened here in Toronto last year,"},{"time":671798,"text":"at the end of the campaign."},{"time":674278,"text":"I was out with a team. It was the end of Movember."},{"time":677719,"text":"We'd had a great campaign, and to be honest, we'd had"},{"time":680472,"text":"our fair share of beer that night, but I said,"},{"time":683246,"text":"\"You know what, I think we've got one more bar left in us.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":686713,"text":"So we piled into a taxi, and this is our taxi driver,"},{"time":690118,"text":"and I was sitting in the back seat, and he turned around"},{"time":692310,"text":"and said, \"Where are you going?\""},{"time":693854,"text":"And I said, \"Hang on, that is an amazing mustache.\""},{"time":696936,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":701343,"text":"And he said, \"I'm doing it for Movember.\" And I said,"},{"time":703279,"text":"\"So am I.\" And I said, \"Tell me your Movember story.\""},{"time":707589,"text":"And he goes, \"Listen, I know it's about men's health,"},{"time":709565,"text":"I know it's about prostate cancer, but this is for breast cancer.\""},{"time":712627,"text":"And I said, \"Okay, that's interesting.\""},{"time":714275,"text":"And he goes, \"Last year, my mom passed away from breast cancer in Sri Lanka,"},{"time":717832,"text":"because we couldn't afford proper treatment for her,\""},{"time":721198,"text":"and he said, \"This mustache is my tribute to my mom.\""},{"time":725510,"text":"And we sort of all choked up in the back of the taxi,"},{"time":728338,"text":"and I didn't tell him who I was, because I didn't think it was appropriate,"},{"time":730871,"text":"and I just shook his hand and I said, \"Thank you so much."},{"time":732814,"text":"Your mom would be so proud.\""},{"time":734158,"text":"And from that moment I realized that Movember"},{"time":736086,"text":"is so much more than a mustache, having a joke."},{"time":739124,"text":"It's about each person coming to this platform,"},{"time":742833,"text":"embracing it in their own way,"},{"time":744963,"text":"and being significant in their own life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748036,"text":"For us now at Movember, we really focus on"},{"time":753311,"text":"three program areas, and having a true impact:"},{"time":757583,"text":"awareness and education,"},{"time":760000,"text":"survivor support programs, and research."},{"time":762787,"text":"Now we always focus, naturally, on how much we raise,"},{"time":766332,"text":"because it's a very tangible outcome, but for me,"},{"time":769453,"text":"awareness and education is more important than the funds we raise,"},{"time":773660,"text":"because I know that is changing and saving lives today,"},{"time":776524,"text":"and it's probably best exampled by"},{"time":778806,"text":"a young guy that I met at South by Southwest"},{"time":781636,"text":"in Austin, Texas, at the start of the year."},{"time":784476,"text":"He came up to me and said, \"Thank you for starting Movember.\""},{"time":787500,"text":"And I said, \"Thank you for doing Movember.\""},{"time":789432,"text":"And I looked at him, and I was like, \"I'm pretty sure you can't grow a mustache.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":793292,"text":"And I said, \"What's your Movember story?\""},{"time":795676,"text":"And he said, \"I grew the worst mustache ever.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":799699,"text":"\"But I went home for Thanksgiving dinner, and pretty quickly"},{"time":802269,"text":"the conversation around the table turned to"},{"time":804269,"text":"what the hell was going on.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":807600,"text":"\"And we talked -- I talked to them about Movember,"},{"time":811748,"text":"and then after that, my dad came up to me, and at the age"},{"time":814093,"text":"of 26, for the first time ever, I had a conversation with my dad"},{"time":818164,"text":"one on one about men's health. I had a conversation"},{"time":821265,"text":"with my dad about prostate cancer, and I learned"},{"time":824388,"text":"that my grandfather had prostate cancer"},{"time":827174,"text":"and I was able to share with my dad that he was"},{"time":830357,"text":"twice as likely to get that disease, and he didn't know that,"},{"time":833380,"text":"and he hadn't been getting screened for it.\""},{"time":835450,"text":"So now, that guy is getting screened for prostate cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838947,"text":"So those conversations, getting men engaged in this,"},{"time":841537,"text":"at whatever age, is so critically important,"},{"time":844332,"text":"and in my view so much more important"},{"time":846354,"text":"than the funds we raise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849469,"text":"Now to the funds we raise, and research,"},{"time":852269,"text":"and how we're redefining research."},{"time":854946,"text":"We fund prostate cancer foundations now in 13 countries."},{"time":859584,"text":"We literally fund hundreds if not thousands of institutions"},{"time":862989,"text":"and researchers around the world, and when we looked"},{"time":865799,"text":"at this more recently, we realized there's a real lack"},{"time":870172,"text":"of collaboration going on even within institutions,"},{"time":874331,"text":"let alone nationally, let alone globally, and this is not unique"},{"time":876684,"text":"to prostate cancer. This is cancer research the world over."},{"time":880104,"text":"And so we said, right, we'd redefined charity. We need"},{"time":883722,"text":"to redefine the way these guys operate. How do we do that?"},{"time":887773,"text":"So what we did was, we created a global action plan,"},{"time":891382,"text":"and we're taking 10 percent of what's raised in each country"},{"time":893199,"text":"now and putting it into a global fund, and we've got"},{"time":895541,"text":"the best prostate cancer scientific minds in the world"},{"time":898277,"text":"that look after that fund,"},{"time":900840,"text":"and they come together each year and identify"},{"time":902949,"text":"the number one priority,"},{"time":905936,"text":"and that, last year, was getting a better screening test."},{"time":909832,"text":"So they identified that as a priority, and then"},{"time":911989,"text":"they've got and recruited now 300 researchers"},{"time":914618,"text":"from around the world that are studying that topic,"},{"time":917302,"text":"essentially the same topic."},{"time":919253,"text":"So now we're funding them to the tune of about"},{"time":921014,"text":"five or six million dollars to collaborate"},{"time":923797,"text":"and bringing them together, and that's a unique thing"},{"time":926405,"text":"in the cancer world, and we know, through that collaboration,"},{"time":929381,"text":"it will accelerate outcomes."},{"time":932773,"text":"And that's how we're redefining the research world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939033,"text":"So, what I know about my Movember journey is that,"},{"time":945677,"text":"with a really creative idea,"},{"time":948819,"text":"with passion, with persistence, and a lot of patience,"},{"time":953236,"text":"four mates, four mustaches,"},{"time":956266,"text":"can inspire a room full of people,"},{"time":958589,"text":"and that room full of people can go on and inspire a city,"},{"time":961502,"text":"and that city is Melbourne, my home."},{"time":963702,"text":"And that city can go on and inspire a state, and that state"},{"time":966965,"text":"can go on and inspire a nation, and beyond that,"},{"time":970538,"text":"you can create a global movement"},{"time":973381,"text":"that is changing the face of men's health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975750,"text":"My name is Adam Garone, and that's my story."},{"time":978125,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}